1
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:55,138
Get down!

2
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:22,531
One!

3
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:01,663
- Rosa! Rosa!
- Quica...

4
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:08,169
Tell me who talked to the police!
Who talked to them? Huh?

5
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:12,132
It had to be that whore
in the market. Please, Quica!

6
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,096
Imagine this:

7
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:26,516
President of Colombia goes on TV
and tells the whole world

8
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,434
he'll never make a deal with you.

9
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:31,980
Now a normal person thinks, "I'm fucked."

10
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:35,858
But Pablo Escobar,
he thinks that's just your opening offer.

11
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:39,112
So the man finds a way to respond.

12
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:44,200
Thanks for accepting the invitation.

13
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:48,454
Forgive me for the hood.

14
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,623
It's for security reasons.

15
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:53,584
- I hope you understand.
- I understand.

16
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,546
Can I offer you something? Coffee, water?

17
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:59,924
No, I'm fine, thank you.

18
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,592
Let's begin, then.

19
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:19,652
- Do you regret going to jail a year ago?
- Absolutely not.

20
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:24,574
In fact, what I regret least
is having escaped.

21
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:27,243
The Special Forces came in
and opened fire.

22
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:29,996
I couldn't risk putting my life
in their hands, right?

23
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,790
However...

24
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:37,253
I hope this interview
makes it clear to the president...

25
00:05:38,546 --> 00:05:42,717
I am willing to return to any prison
in the District of Antioquia.

26
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:46,304
The most modest and the most humble.

27
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:49,199
But before that, I have to examine
the conditions they are going to put me in

28
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:53,978
because, look, it would be easy,
for example, for someone to rig a car bomb

29
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,855
that would explode when I arrived.

30
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:59,400
And how did Gaviria take Pablo's offer?

31
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:04,447
I think it's safe to say
that he didn't really care for it.

32
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:07,992
But it wasn't just Gaviria
Pablo was talking to.

33
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:11,579
In his mind, he was also negotiating
with the leader of the free world.

34
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:16,751
It turns out that my problem
turned into a political problem.

35
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:19,420
It appears that I am very important

36
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,744
to the re-election
of the President of the United States.

37
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:26,385
You see, the problem was,
George Bush had his own plans for Escobar.

38
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:27,970
We will, for the first time,

39
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:32,225
make available the appropriate resources
of America's armed forces.

40
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:36,020
And for the drug kingpins,
the death penalty.

41
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:40,483
And with a commander in chief
who used to be the head of the CIA,

42
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,151
well, you can use your imagination

43
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:45,696
as to what "appropriate resources"
might mean.

44
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:49,575
He started by appointing a new ambassador.

45
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:53,579
Badass former Navy man, Arthur Crosby...

46
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:59,043
who specialized in Latin American affairs
and counterterrorism.

47
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,924
Next, he dug into his old CIA Rolodex,

48
00:07:05,007 --> 00:07:08,427
where there was no shortage of guys
who knew how to fight dirty.

49
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:12,723
And he sent us one of those, too.

50
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:20,731
Lastly, and what Peña and I like to call
his own personal "fuck you" to us...

51
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:26,112
he sent us something
he thought we must need: a boss.

52
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:31,701
Now just how long that person
would be my boss remained to be seen.

53
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:37,957
I will always be ready to pay for
my mistakes and accept a humble jail cell

54
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:41,252
when my rights are respected

55
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:46,215
and they guarantee me that I will not
be transferred anywhere for any reason.

56
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:51,929
Do you acknowledge that
you have committed crimes in the past,

57
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:54,140
or that you ordered someone's death?

58
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:04,775
That answer one could
only give to a priest.

59
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:06,903
In a confessional.

60
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:15,368
Marietta.

61
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:17,413
- What's up?
- What happened?

62
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:22,460
It looks like they killed them.
I think there were six or seven girls.

63
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:24,629
Who would do something so horrible?

64
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:38,100
Are you, by nature, violent and proud?

65
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:42,313
Those who know me
know I have a great sense of humor.

66
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:46,776
I would say that I'm a happy man.

67
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:48,986
I've always been happy.
I've always been optimistic.

68
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,863
I've always had faith in life.

69
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:53,574
I always sing in the shower.

70
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:56,827
How do you think the story
of Pablo Escobar will end?

71
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:06,587
Well... one can never know.
I can only hope for the best.

72
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:15,012
I would like to die on my own two feet.

73
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,892
In the year 3047.

74
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,563
My title might be "ambassador,"

75
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:26,232
but that's some bullshit
politician's word.

76
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:28,609
I know what it means
to be on the front lines.

77
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:34,407
And everybody in this room wants
the same thing: to take down Escobar.

78
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:38,911
Now as a veteran of numerous conflicts,
I learned one immutable truth:

79
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,877
the only way to succeed
is by working together,

80
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:44,792
by communicating,
by sharing intelligence and collaborating.

81
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,419
Understood?

82
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:51,799
Uh, this is Claudia Messina.
She is the new DEA country attaché.

83
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:55,094
She'll be taking over all DEA operations
in-country. Messina?

84
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:56,971
Thank you, Ambassador.

85
00:09:57,054 --> 00:10:02,810
The DEA will be opening field offices
in Cali, Cartagena and Barranquilla.

86
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:05,313
As far as the Medellín team is concerned,

87
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:09,191
they will be housed out of
CNP headquarters until further notice.

88
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:11,902
But only after some personnel changes
have been made.

89
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:14,739
All right, now as far as
long-term intelligence is concerned,

90
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:18,826
that's under the purview of the CIA,
the station chief, Bill Stechner.

91
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:20,554
Bill, you have anything you'd like to add?

92
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:21,954
I'm good.

93
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:28,961
- All right, who's here from Centra Spike?
- I am, sir. Edward Jacoby.

94
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,398
All right, let's get Centra Spike
back in the air immediately.

95
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:33,466
I want to know every word
these assholes say

96
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:36,429
and all information flows through me
and I will disseminate as I see fit.

97
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:37,595
Yes, sir.

98
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:42,308
When Escobar sticks his fucking head out,
we're gonna nail that son of a bitch.

99
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:46,187
What about him? Other than
the fact that he wasn't here today.

100
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,439
Well, I suggested that he stay home.

101
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:52,026
You mentioned making some changes.
What exactly does that mean?

102
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:54,528
It means I'm making some changes.

103
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,965
Murphy's a good agent.
He's done a lot of good work down here.

104
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,074
Yeah.

105
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,036
Looks like it.

106
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:09,210
Do you have any idea
the strings that were pulled

107
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:10,961
to get that guy not to press charges?

108
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,398
Sounds to me like the guy
would've had a dog sniffing up his ass

109
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:15,622
before he got on the plane.
Maybe Steve did him a favor.

110
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,551
Was that a thank you?

111
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:23,140
Be straight with me, Agent Peña,
and I'll be straight with you.

112
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:25,976
I don't need a guy like that
making my life more difficult.

113
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:28,062
- And making the DEA look bad.
- Ma'am...

114
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:31,232
Messina. Or boss.

115
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:32,900
We've been down here a long time.

116
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:34,985
You've been down here all of what,
two hours?

117
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,991
It may not make the front page, but...

118
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:44,036
a lot of the intel we have
is because of Steve.

119
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:47,998
He's a good man.
He's going through some shit right now.

120
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:49,976
You know, he was at the airport

121
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,000
to stop his wife from leaving the country
with their kid. He didn't make it.

122
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:57,216
Add that to watching Escobar
build a five-star prison

123
00:11:57,299 --> 00:11:59,093
and then walking out the back door.

124
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:04,640
We both deserve to see this through...

125
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,143
boss.

126
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:21,532
Have you, uh... had anything to eat
in the last 24 hours?

127
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:25,161
This new boss... Messina...

128
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:27,246
what do you know about her?

129
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:30,708
Only what I've heard.
She's out of New York.

130
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:34,962
Doesn't put up with any shit.

131
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:38,132
Fuck! Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

132
00:12:38,215 --> 00:12:39,341
Am I out?

133
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:42,386
I don't know.

134
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:48,517
Well, I ain't ready to go home yet, Javi.
I'll tell ya that.

135
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:51,518
Damn it! She's fucking...

136
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:57,026
Take a shower. Sober up.

137
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:58,319
Talk to you.

138
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:07,411
Look behind you. Watch out for that guy.

139
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,498
That's it.

140
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:12,833
Smash the telephone booth.

141
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,252
Get the pipe.

142
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:17,213
I already know, Dad.

143
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:19,131
You have to get it.

144
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:22,676
And what's that, a woman?

145
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,845
I'm about to fight a woman or what?

146
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:28,098
- Her name's Nora.
- Oh, yeah, what's her name?

147
00:13:28,182 --> 00:13:29,642
Nora.

148
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:32,728
Boss, excuse the interruption.
One moment, please.

149
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:35,147
How do you...?

150
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:45,574
What about the laboratories?

151
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:49,411
It's been difficult
to find the Moncada laboratories, boss.

152
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,373
And the ones that we find,
we can't get inside.

153
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:55,417
There are police checkpoints everywhere.

154
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:58,379
We lost four men
trying to get through one.

155
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:01,715
Sons of bitches.

156
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:05,135
And what about Judy Moncada?

157
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:10,432
We can't find her anywhere. Or Don Berna.

158
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:11,934
Find her.

159
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:14,103
Yes, sir.

160
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,525
And you, boys?

161
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:22,653
- Everything is good, boss.
- All good, boss.

162
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:25,030
- How are you, Limón?
- Very good, sir.

163
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:26,907
- How are you feeling?
- Very good, boss.

164
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,742
- Comfortable?
- Thank you. Very good.

165
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:29,827
Good.

166
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:33,205
I'm going to teach you something.

167
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:38,210
There is nothing lower than a rat.

168
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:46,051
And if we let the rats run free,
the streets will be filled with them.

169
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:48,095
- Understand me?
- Yes, boss.

170
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:52,057
Give me one second. One second.

171
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,976
Boss, excuse me. It's Fernando.

172
00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:59,607
- Tell me, Fernando.
- Your interview clearly worked, Don Pablo.

173
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:02,192
Palace wants to meet with me right away.

174
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,945
You heard that, brother? Hm?

175
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:10,200
- We have to finish our little job.
- But we already finished it, right?

176
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:13,495
No, brother, there's still one left.

177
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:15,831
But you already killed all the whores.

178
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,417
I'm not talking about whores, brother.

179
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,837
Why her?

180
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:25,215
- She did everything we told her to.
- Someone talked to the police.

181
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,760
Yeah, it was those fucking whores.

182
00:15:27,843 --> 00:15:31,180
She is someone I can trust, man.

183
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:34,600
You can trust her, but I can't.

184
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:36,060
Move it.

185
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:39,897
Quica.

186
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:46,445
I'm not going to tell you again, brother.
And we've got some shit we gotta do first.

187
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:48,489
- Good day.
- Good day.

188
00:15:48,572 --> 00:15:52,117
I have a meeting with the president.

189
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:53,744
I am Fernando Duque.

190
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:01,251
Your meeting is not
with the president, Mr. Duque.

191
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:02,544
How's that?

192
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:07,967
- With the vice minister, then?
- No, sir.

193
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:11,637
The information I have here says
your meeting is with the attorney general.

194
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:16,141
My apologies, Mr. Duque.

195
00:16:19,269 --> 00:16:21,188
Now, Gaviria had made it clear

196
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:24,400
that the government
was not to negotiate with Escobar.

197
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:26,902
But Colombia Attorney General
Gustavo de Greiff

198
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,613
didn't give a shit
what the president wanted.

199
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:35,786
Unlike the US, where the attorney general
is appointed by the president,

200
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:39,790
in Colombia, the Supreme Court
chooses the attorney general,

201
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:42,292
whether the president likes it or not.

202
00:16:43,627 --> 00:16:48,507
And in the case of Gustavo de Greiff,
you bet your ass Gaviria didn't.

203
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:51,135
Mr. Duque...

204
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:56,682
I believe the whole world
has the right to a fair trial.

205
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:03,147
Pablo Escobar has the same rights
as any other Colombian.

206
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:09,236
If he has committed a crime,
he must be judged and indicted.

207
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:12,322
He can't be hunted and killed
like an animal.

208
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:15,701
Mr. De Greiff,

209
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:21,790
everything you're telling me I find...
fascinating.

210
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,878
However, I don't...

211
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:30,174
I don't buckle under the pressure
of the Americans...

212
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:34,136
like Gaviria, Mr. Duque.

213
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,221
Uh-huh.

214
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:38,557
Then that means that...

215
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:44,021
you would consider...
making a deal with Pablo.

216
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:47,941
I am saying that Colombia...

217
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:51,528
has been at war far too long.

218
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,572
Of course.

219
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:02,956
The Americans are bringing in new people.

220
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:07,586
Different faces but, ultimately,
with the same motivation.

221
00:18:09,713 --> 00:18:12,716
They are using us
to advance their political agenda.

222
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:14,760
Perhaps.

223
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:19,181
But the reality is we have to accept help
wherever it comes from.

224
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:23,352
And right now,
the gringos are very limited,

225
00:18:23,435 --> 00:18:25,521
confined to Carlos Holguín
and the embassy.

226
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:30,317
On the other hand, Pablo Escobar
is gaining ground, gathering more support.

227
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,569
Everyone is helping him in Medellín.

228
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:36,281
- A long manhunt plays into his hands.
- Let's talk about Medellín.

229
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:45,499
Colonel Pinzón basically
has Escobar surrounded.

230
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,711
Do you think we'll succeed?

231
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:58,595
Listen, thanks for talking
to Messina, man.

232
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,765
I mean it. You saved my ass.

233
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:08,105
One more fuck-up, Murphy...

234
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,440
Oh, I know.

235
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,485
Is it gonna happen again?

236
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,406
I don't know.

237
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:23,162
DEA politics weren't
the only thing we had to navigate.

238
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:25,873
The Pinzón plan was in full effect.

239
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,918
He was doubling down on police presence.

240
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:35,299
Medellín was under martial law
and the base of Carlos Holguín

241
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:37,050
would look like Fort Apache.

242
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:42,097
Me and Javi were officially guests
of the CNP.

243
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:44,308
With all the comforts and amenities

244
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:48,187
that a guest of the National
