00:38:04,073 --> 00:38:09,287
if people are actually after you,
that's not paranoid. That's just smart.

491
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:12,331
Peña! Messina!

492
00:38:34,645 --> 00:38:36,188
He was here.

493
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:46,240
Go ahead, come in.

494
00:38:51,037 --> 00:38:52,371
The bedrooms...

495
00:38:54,540 --> 00:38:56,167
they're on the right.

496
00:39:10,056 --> 00:39:11,974
Everything is okay, Tata.

497
00:39:12,058 --> 00:39:15,436
No, Pablo.
This time everything is not okay.

498
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:18,939
Sweetheart, if Pablo
says everything is okay,

499
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:21,183
- it's because everything is...
- Was I talking to you?

500
00:39:23,486 --> 00:39:25,654
I'm talking to my husband.

501
00:39:27,656 --> 00:39:29,867
That was very close, Pablo.

502
00:39:29,950 --> 00:39:31,869
And tomorrow, what?

503
00:39:31,952 --> 00:39:34,288
Do you want your children
to watch those men kill you?

504
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,415
No one is going to die, Tata.

505
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:39,627
I am dealing with it.

506
00:39:40,669 --> 00:39:41,921
How, Pablo?

507
00:39:42,713 --> 00:39:44,090
Tell me how.

508
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:47,301
Negotiating?

509
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:50,763
Yesterday, they nearly killed you
for negotiating.

510
00:39:52,431 --> 00:39:55,226
If you are going to fix everything,
fix it for good.

511
00:40:07,655 --> 00:40:09,281
Don't worry.

512
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:24,839
You know,
in all the years I chased Escobar,

513
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:28,050
I could count on one hand
the times we almost had him.

514
00:40:28,134 --> 00:40:30,344
And each time, we forgot
the two most important things

515
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:32,221
we already knew about him:

516
00:40:32,304 --> 00:40:34,098
Close doesn't count.

517
00:40:34,181 --> 00:40:38,227
And Pablo is never more dangerous
than when you almost have him.

518
00:41:06,338 --> 00:41:09,633
With all the cops on the street,
it was easy to forget...

519
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:13,679
this was still Escobar's town.

520
00:41:17,349 --> 00:41:21,312
He tolerated it all
in the interest of negotiations.

521
00:41:23,314 --> 00:41:25,357
Chasing a man and his family
out of their home

522
00:41:25,441 --> 00:41:27,193
in the middle of the night?

523
00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:29,320
That wasn't a negotiation.

524
00:41:29,403 --> 00:41:30,403
To Escobar...

525
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:33,324
well, that was an act of war.

526
00:41:33,407 --> 00:41:34,407
Ready.

527
00:41:37,661 --> 00:41:40,706
Boss, everybody is ready.
What's the order?

528
00:41:41,582 --> 00:41:42,750
Do it.

529
00:41:43,667 --> 00:41:44,877
Yes, sir.

530
00:41:48,005 --> 00:41:49,965
- Huh? What's up?
- Ready.

531
00:41:50,049 --> 00:41:51,467
- All right.
- Okay.

532
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:56,180
We're ready, sir.

533
00:42:24,917 --> 00:42:26,210
Come.

534
00:42:59,493 --> 00:43:01,954
Step on it!

535
00:43:54,048 --> 00:43:55,424
Do it, brother.

536
00:43:56,759 --> 00:43:58,719
It's cold, you fucking fag!

537
00:43:58,802 --> 00:44:02,306
Kill him! Do it, bitch! Kill him!

538
00:44:02,389 --> 00:44:03,599
Aah!

539
00:45:20,467 --> 00:45:21,467
Peña!

